's fiery end in the Roman destruction of Jerusalem, she brings this vibrant apostolic community to life. Fredriksen offers a vivid portrait both of this temple†'centered messianic movement and of the bedrock convictions that animated and sustained it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 0aJewsxHistoryy586 B.C.-70 A.D. 7aRELIGION / Ancient.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300240740423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300240740.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles